description:
Reflection, Repentance and the Latter Rain: Part 1 - Introduction to an overview of the shaking and the latter rain, including the prophecy of Malachi and how Gods people must learn again, what it means to be set apart, prior to receiving the outpouring of the Spirit.  Also included, is how the story of Samson reveals truths about these last day events. Presented by Tim Saxton, Associate Speaker for White Horse Media.

chapters.title: The Latter rain, in its fullness is associated with the Loud Cry Message of Revelation 18 and lightens the world with Heavens final warning.
Latter rain comes in its fullness at the commencement of earth's little time of trouble.
The Latter Rain is poured out after the troubles of earth shake God's church to its very foundation.
The shaking of the church, produces a repentance and drawing together of God's people unlike anything since apostolic times.
